{"LanguageCode":"en","Chapter":100,"Index":"100","Name":"Al-Aadiyat","TranslatedName":"The Courser","ArabicName":"سُوْرَةُ العٰدِيٰتِ","Revelation":"Mecca","RevelationOrder":14,"VerseCount":11,"SajdaCount":0,"JuzStart":30,"JuzEnd":30,"VerseStart":6147,"VerseEnd":6157,"ManzilStart":7,"ManzilEnd":7,"RukuStart":542,"RukuEnd":542,"MaqraStart":239,"MaqraEnd":240,"PageStart":599,"PageEnd":600,"Summaries":["<p>11 verses in 1 section. The Surah tells us the ungratefulness of man and where it leads him. It describes the wild and unruly life style of the Arabs before Islam. It also reminds us that Allah is aware of all the hidden secrets of human souls and He will expose them on the Day of Judgment.</p>"],"Verses":[{"Verse":1,"Text":"وَٱلۡعَٰدِيَٰتِ ضَبۡحٗا","End":"١"},{"Verse":2,"Text":"فَٱلۡمُورِيَٰتِ قَدۡحٗا","End":"٢"},{"Verse":3,"Text":"فَٱلۡمُغِيرَٰتِ صُبۡحٗا","End":"٣"},{"Verse":4,"Text":"فَأَثَرۡنَ بِهِۦ نَقۡعٗا","End":"٤"},{"Verse":5,"Text":"فَوَسَطۡنَ بِهِۦ جَمۡعًا","End":"٥"},{"Verse":6,"Text":"إِنَّ ٱلۡإِنسَٰنَ لِرَبِّهِۦ لَكَنُودٞ","End":"٦"},{"Verse":7,"Text":"وَإِنَّهُۥ عَلَىٰ ذَٰلِكَ لَشَهِيدٞ","End":"٧"},{"Verse":8,"Text":"وَإِنَّهُۥ لِحُبِّ ٱلۡخَيۡرِ لَشَدِيدٌ","End":"٨"},{"Verse":9,"Text":"۞أَفَلَا يَعۡلَمُ إِذَا بُعۡثِرَ مَا فِي ٱلۡقُبُورِ","End":"٩"},{"Verse":10,"Text":"وَحُصِّلَ مَا فِي ٱلصُّدُورِ","End":"١٠"},{"Verse":11,"Text":"إِنَّ رَبَّهُم بِهِمۡ يَوۡمَئِذٖ لَّخَبِيرُۢ","End":"١١"}],"Translations":[]}